growth must be <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">zero</NUMEX>. While <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Siegel</ENAMEX>'s point fits the simplest introductory
economic <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">models</ENAMEX>, it is contradicted by the facts: <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Historical</ENAMEX> data on dividends
reveal significant real growth of dividends per share. For example, in the
